#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-composition-patterns/rules/state-decouple-implementation.md savings=-8%
M||tx|---
M||titl|Decouple State Management from UI
M||impa|md
M||impa|enables swapping state implementations w/o changing UI
M||tags|composition, state, architecture
M||tx|---
M|Deco|tx|The pr cp shd be the only place that knows how state is managed.
M|Deco|tx|UI cp consume the context if—they don't know if state comes from
M|Deco|tx|useState, Zustand, or a server sync.
M|Deco|**In|**
M|Deco|tx|```tsx
M|Deco|func|{ channelId: string }) {
M|Deco|tx|// UI cp knows abt global state implementation
M|Deco|tx|const state = useGlobalChannelState(channelId)
M|Deco|tx|const { submit, updateInput } = useChannelSync(channelId)
M|Deco|tx|return (
M|Deco|tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|Deco|tx|<Composer.Input
M|Deco|tx|value={state.input}
M|Deco|tx|onChange={(text) => sync.updateInput(text)}
M|Deco|tx|/>
M|Deco|tx|<Composer.Submit onPress={() => sync.submit()} />
M|Deco|tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|Deco|tx|)
M|Deco|tx|}
M|Deco|tx|```
M|Deco|**Co|**
M|Deco|tx|```tsx
M|Deco|tx|// pr handles all state management details
M|Deco|tx|fn ChannelProvider({
M|Deco|tx|channelId,
M|Deco|tx|children,
M|Deco|}|{
M|Deco|chan|string
M|Deco|chil|rc.ReactNode
M|Deco|tx|}) {
M|Deco|tx|const { state, up, submit } = useGlobalChannel(channelId)
M|Deco|tx|const inputRef = useRef(null)
M|Deco|tx|return (
M|Deco|tx|<Composer.pr
M|Deco|tx|state={state}
M|Deco|tx|actions={{ up, submit }}
M|Deco|tx|meta={{ inputRef }}
M|Deco|tx|>
M|Deco|tx|{children}
M|Deco|tx|</Composer.pr>
M|Deco|tx|)
M|Deco|tx|}
M|Deco|tx|// UI cp only knows abt the context if
M|Deco|tx|fn ChannelComposer() {
M|Deco|tx|return (
M|Deco|tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|Deco|tx|<Composer.Header />
M|Deco|tx|<Composer.Input />
M|Deco|tx|<Composer.Footer>
M|Deco|tx|<Composer.Submit />
M|Deco|tx|</Composer.Footer>
M|Deco|tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|Deco|tx|)
M|Deco|tx|}
M|Deco|tx|// Usage
M|Deco|func|{ channelId: string }) {
M|Deco|tx|return (
M|Deco|tx|<ChannelProvider channelId={channelId}>
M|Deco|tx|<ChannelComposer />
M|Deco|tx|</ChannelProvider>
M|Deco|tx|)
M|Deco|tx|}
M|Deco|tx|```
M|Deco|**Di|**
M|Deco|tx|```tsx
M|Deco|tx|// Local state for ephemeral forms
M|Deco|tx|fn ForwardMessageProvider({ children }) {
M|Deco|tx|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|Deco|tx|const forwardMessage = useForwardMessage()
M|Deco|tx|return (
M|Deco|tx|<Composer.pr
M|Deco|tx|state={state}
M|Deco|acti|setState, submit: forwardMessage }}
M|Deco|tx|>
M|Deco|tx|{children}
M|Deco|tx|</Composer.pr>
M|Deco|tx|)
M|Deco|tx|}
M|Deco|tx|// Global synced state for channels
M|Deco|tx|fn ChannelProvider({ channelId, children }) {
M|Deco|tx|const { state, up, submit } = useGlobalChannel(channelId)
M|Deco|tx|return (
M|Deco|tx|<Composer.pr state={state} actions={{ up, submit }}>
M|Deco|tx|{children}
M|Deco|tx|</Composer.pr>
M|Deco|tx|)
M|Deco|tx|}
M|Deco|tx|```
M|Deco|tx|The same `Composer.Input` cp works w/ both pr bc it only
M|Deco|tx|depends on the context if, not the implementation.